      <section eId="sec_7_5_1">
        <num>7-5.1</num>
        <heading>Definitions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_7_5_1__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A "beneficiary" is a person who is described by a depositor as a\nperson for whom a trust account is established or maintained.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_7_5_1__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A "depositor" is a person in whose name a trust account subject to\nthis part is established or maintained.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_7_5_1__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A "financial institution" is a bank, trust company, national\nbanking association, savings bank, industrial bank, private banker,\nforeign banking corporation, federal savings and loan association, a\nsavings institution chartered and supervised as a savings and loan or\nsimilar institution under federal law or the laws of a state, a federal\ncredit union, or a credit union chartered and supervised under the laws\nof a state.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_7_5_1__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A "trust account" includes a savings, share, certificate or\ndeposit account in a financial institution established by a depositor\ndescribing himself as trustee for another, other than a depositor\ndescribing himself as acting under a will, trust instrument or other\ninstrument, court order or decree.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
